From the angle addition formula,
\begin{align*}
\tan 60^\circ &= \tan (20^\circ + 40^\circ) \\
&= \frac{\tan 20^\circ + \tan 40^\circ}{1 - \tan 20^\circ \tan 40^\circ},
\end{align*}so
\begin{align*}
\tan 20^\circ + \tan 40^\circ + \sqrt{3} \tan 20^\circ \tan 40^\circ &= \tan 60^\circ (1 - \tan 20^\circ \tan 40^\circ) + \sqrt{3} \tan 20^\circ \tan 40^\circ \\
&= \sqrt{3} (1 - \tan 20^\circ \tan 40^\circ) + \sqrt{3} \tan 20^\circ \tan 40^\circ \\
&= \boxed{\sqrt{3}}.
\end{align*}

